07/10/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- War crimes prosecutors announced on Tuesday (October 6th) that charges have been filed against five Serbian citizens, for actions committed in Medak, Croatia, in September 1991. 
The former militia members are charged with the inhumane treatment of a Croatian police officer. 
They will remain free pending trial.
In other news Tuesday, parliament began discussing a Defence Strategy and a National Security Strategy. 
Defence Minister Dragan Sutanovac, who presented the documents, said they are crucial to protecting Serbia's national interests. 
He described Kosovo's unilaterally-declared independence as the main security threat. 
(Tanjug, B92, Beta, Medjunarodni Radio Srbija, RTS, AP - 06/10/09)
